context_history.content: I want to learn about: html. DO NOT greet me. Immediately start lesson Step 1 by explaining the core concept on the whiteboard.

HTML, or HyperText Markup Language, serves as the structural skeleton of every webpage on the internet. It uses 'tags' to label pieces of content so the browser knows whether something is a heading, a paragraph, or an image.

visual_content.detail: HTML Code, Browser, Visual Webpage, The browser reads the code and renders it as a structured page.
